@{u} Why FreeWare/GiftWare and no $hareware? @{uu}

Actually I'm every bit as greedy or maybe even more than other coders who make
shareware, however I'm also realist and understand that there is no big paying
mass for so incomplete product as DreamTerm. It is also unlikely that I ever
polish everything to be 100% or add most basic features required so this
situation will remain as it is now. I believe that you cannot make money from
shareware if you don't have good register sites, user support and some real
demand for product. And as there is several other freeware/shareware
terminals, I think that market is full. Though for some strange reason this
program satisfies my every need... :-) Hopefully yours too and if not feel
free to mail me any ideas, though don't expect instant replies or
implementations.
@endnode

@node "doc_faq" "Frequently Asked Questions"
@{b}Q:@{ub} VirusZ naggs about changed vectors

You're using Hardware serial option, it uses Exec routine which changes
interrupt vectors. If only Serial Out and Serial In is changed you have
nothing to worry. To remove those requesters just pop up Background
Preferences window in VirusZ and uncheck Exec Interrupts Surveillance.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Why system screen is so slow sometimes?

This is mostly system's fault which is somewhat slow changing colors &
positions (they are changed lot in ANSI drawings). Hardware screen is more
than adequate work-around if you don't own one of those fancy and expensive
graphics cards. With A1200/A4000 it probably can print much more chars in
second than serial port is capable receiving. Remember that with old chipset
you cannot use 16-color screen, use 8-color screen instead. If you have
A1200/A4000 put 'Enable AGA Burst' on and you have 2x bandwidth which offers
possibility to use 16-color hardware screen with any DTE. This switch is there
because there is no official information about AGA and how to enable 2x/4x
bandwidth modes.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Why to use internal ANSI when there is XEm?

Internal is much faster and uses pen allocation which will result better look
in normal Workbench screen. However if you need full DEC-VT emulation then
VT340 is better choice.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Why this wonderful program is free?

Because I know that you are nice person just about to send generous gift to me
but earthquake/avalanche/nuclear war is delaying your action.

@{b}Q: @{ub}Some applications opened on DTerm's public screen look like crap.

They are crap. Most old 1.0 aware programs do not bother to find where system
pens really are, try 'Keep Workbench colors' option.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Why MUI window font sometimes is reduced to unreadable size?

You probably opened window on tiny screen, minimum size where all windows are
designed to work is 640x256 with topaz/8. If this is annoying try changing
tiny font in MUI-preferences to something really small.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Some predefined MUI-prefs will cause windows to use wrong colors

For some reason those configurations use fixed color index from screen
palette, this is totally lame as there is no rule that I must put some stupid
color to some fixed location (0,1,...,n). So if you are creating nice
backgrounds etc. be careful not to use Colormap for pens in MUI-preferences,
instead use either System or RGB. In fact I don't understand why
MUI-preferences even allows to use fixed locations... It may be that MUI
expects every program to use its own screen manager which is not useful for my
terminal program. 

@{b}More technical explanation@{ub}

These 'problems' come from the fact that when keep workbench colors option is
off (it should always be) DreamTerm allocates first 2-16 pens to use with
emulation/console, this is done to optimize scrolling etc. in more colorful
screens. Also every system pen is remapped to best possible match so other
programs cannot trust that some particular system pen is in same position
where it is in the Workbench screen. This is completely legal and MUI can
handle it as long you don't use that ugly Colormap option! (Well... for some
reason which I cannot understand, includes state that background pen should
always be 0. Fortunately MUI and most other programs which can handle changed
system pen positions in public screen also understand that there is no sense
for that rule and happily use whatever pen is assigned to background.) Anyway
if problems arise you can allways use Keep Workbench colors option.

@{b}Q:@{ub} Review buffer loses lines even that it is not full.

Review will automatically delete old lines when it cannot allocate space for
new lines, this can also happen if other parts need memory and it is not
available.

@{b}Q:@{ub} DreamTerm quits suddenly or freezes

This is most propably due @{b}very@{ub} low memory, there are some critical parts which
must have small amount of memory and cannot fail. This will mostly cause
freeze as there is no memory to display requester, however if this happen free
system memory and freeze should go away. Anyway, this condition is rare and
should not happen at all...

@{b}Q:@{ub} I can't understand how to use finnish DreamTerm

Uh, as there is not finnish documentation it is not easy to see what some
finnish option is in english. Anyway, as menu/gadget order is same it is
barely possible to find explanation for them (At least if this guide would be
compelete or easy to understand:-).

@{b}Q:@{ub} What is the meaning of life?

I don't know, I don't care, just waste your life in playing BatMUD.
@endnode

@node "doc_terminology" "Terminology"
@{u} global @{uu}

Option which cannot be configured from phonebook entry. I created these
because there are some options which make no sense to be configurable from
every entry. Anyway, if you feel that some of them should be moved to entry
then let me know and I might do it.

@{u} Profile @{uu}

To avoid 'configurable == configure everything' effect there is so called
profile which is used to share settings between phonebook entries. It simply
means that you can select for every phonebook entry which settings are copied
from profile. Generally you should try to use it as much as possible and use
local values only for phone numbers, passwords etc. If you do so it will be
much easier to change some setting only from profile when needed (although I
may code handy @{"multiediting" link "doc_future" 0} someday).

Note: Every time when I add new options they will be in profile state in
      old phonebook entries.)
@endnode

@node "doc_mui" "MUI bugs and strange features"
This section describes some problems in MUI 3.3 which I cannot pass with some
clever kludge. I'm not listing those kludges which I have done in order to
make things work as planned despite some very strange 'features' in MUI. Of
course I reserve the right to be just stupid coder who don't understand
documentation and is blaming others for his own errors. I also want to
complain little about autodocs as they don't explain all necessary details.
:)

@{u} Strange box in middle of the custom screen @{uu}

If you change configuration with MUI-preferences little box will appear in
middle of screen, this is actually small window which normally is behind
console. For some reason MUI will pop it up when changing config, I could fix
this with checking window every second or so but decided not to as it would
marginally slow things... For interested that dummy window is there to make
MUI request's possible.

@{u} Iconify leaves custom screen behind @{uu}

DreamTerm will always close window when you press iconify but serial will
remain active if you have called bbs and modem is still online. Note that
custom screen is not closed because MUI will close/open window before
notifying program about user action. And as you can imagine system do not like
windows to open on non-exist screen. Very annoying as MUI do not allow program
to control this at all.

@{u} No popup objects @{uu}

For some reason MUI will open any other popup object than window to wrong
screen if you use your own custom screen, due that there is no popup objects
in DreamTerm. This could be passed to configure public screen to use DTerm.1
but as it so hard for average user to remember I decided not to use popups.
Well, do that anyway and MUI configuration screen will open to right screen
when using that magic button in window. Actually I haven't yet check if 3.3
works, somehow it feels that it is my mistake anyway... :P

@{u} Extra @{uu}

This is only for MUI programmers. There is bug or feature which comes from
fact that MUI do not change anything if data is already same, this leads in
some cases for problems when you supply different data but you happen to have
same address for that data. For example MUIA_Window_Screen needs different
address if you want MUI to really read new screen values. Very confusing as
when you close old screen and open new screen immediately after that there is
BIG chance that screen structure address is same... This seems to affect all
tags which use pointer to some structures. Uh, didn't have time to check if
this affects 3.3 also, propably does.
@endnode

