@node "doc_cryptology" "Cryptology"
Before using phonebook crypting read this carefully, you also should read
documents of library which you plan to use. And if you really are interested
about security, crypting, politics, patents etc. you may want to read PGP
documentation.

@{u} Saving @{uu}

DreamTerm will first save phonebook without crypting to its temporary
directory and then crypt it using some xpk library, after that non-crypted
file will be overwritten and deleted. This is little bit risky as some
fragments may be left in disk, so ideally temporary directory should be ram
disk. Crypt mode will also delete name, phone, password and function keys from
current settings before saving them. Logfile or download list are not
automatically disabled as someone may want to use them.

@{u} Loading @{uu}

Generally same as saving. Note that password is NOT checked and so phonebook
loading may fail without warning if password is wrong.

@{u} General @{uu}

You must not use ENCO library as it is very unsafe! I advice you to use
IDEA.100 which probably is the best algorithm available on Amiga.

In some countries it could be crime to keep your privacy as government may
want to have total control over your mind.
@endnode

@node "doc_emulations" "Emulations"
@{u} Ansi/VT102 @{uu}

Internal ANSI emulation with some VT102 commands, best choice if you use only
bbs systems. DreamTerm will automatically try to allocate needed pens for
defined colors even if you use public screen, actual colors will depend which
are available.

Use XEm VT340 if you need full DEC-VT emulation. 

@{u} Hex @{uu}

Translates incoming chars to hex, can be some use if you need to know what you
really receive.

@{u} XEm 2.0 @{uu}

Unfortunately you cannot use external emulations with hardware screen.
Configuration is also little bit complicated because xem documentation do not
say anything about colors. Due that DreamTerm's xem implementation will always
use first x colors which you can specify if you use custom screen but not when
Workbench screen is used. So you lose flexibility of automatic pen allocation.
Note that incoming char conversion is disabled but output (keyboard/send
ascii) is still on. It is also possible that xem will not use font which is
specified in charset. Another thing is that sometimes whole screen/window is
not used, this is due the problem that DreamTerm cannot know which font xem
will use and thus size is mostly wrong if you use other than 8x8 fonts. Also
with some libraries you can expect trouble when using in public screen
window.

Tech: I could use XEmulatorInfo() but it has only console size, probably
author expected that everybody uses 8x8 fonts forever. :)

When you change xem library version you should reconfigure emulation because
old options may be changed. First use reset button and after that change
options, otherwise library may get confused. For interested this is due the
fact that DreamTerm will keep xem configuration files within its own config
files and extract them when needed using XEmulatorPreferences() command.
@endnode

@node "doc_string commands" "String commands "
Code explanation is extracted directly from my source. As you can see old ^x,
\x and new %rx or %vx codes are usable in strings and you can use them in many
strings (hopefully marked in relative parts of documentation). There is also
one code (~) which is interpreted only if string is sent to serial. Your
string is handled as if it was format string (simplified!) and it supports
following options for %rx or %vx types:

 %[flags][width]type

 flags  - only one allowed. '-' specifies left justification.
 width  - field width (or better: absolute field size)
          If the first character is a '0' and type is numerical (%vx), the
          field will be padded with leading 0's. If type is string (%rx)
          then it is limit.
 type   - some rx/vx type (ra, rb, rc etc.)

Note that resulting string is maximum 255 bytes long so if you for example
specify many download dirs (%rd) then last ones propably are cutted away, also
it is mostly better not supply field width or limit as they can be confusing
to use.

For example "%06vd %rd %ru" would create string "057600 download: upload:" if
your current dte rate was 57600, download path download: and upload path
upload:. In some future version I may (don't believe, editors note:-) create
new string class which would have button where you could select those cryptic
codes from plain language list.

(" are only to show where format string starts and ends)

 *
 * Converte DreamTerm string codes to string.
 *
 * str   : destination, maximum of STRSIZE is written (includes 0 byte)!
 * format: formatstring
 *
 * Note: ~ is not translated as it is used only in strings which are sent
 *       to serial.
 *
 *         \n  = linefeed  (0x0a)  (char )
 *         \r  = return    (0x0d)  (char )
 *         \t  = tab       (0x09)  (char )
 *         \b  = backspace (0x08)  (char )
 *         \e  = escape    (0x1b)  (char )
 *         \\  = \                 (char )
 *         ^x  = control           (char )
 *         ^^  = ^                 (char )
 *
 * These are special which just copy from current settings, %vx is treated
 * as numerical and %rx as string.
 *
 *         %va = current rxd speed
 *         %vb = current txd speed
 *         %vc = current cost
 *         %vd = current dte
 *         %vf = current overruns
 *         %vk = current columns
 *         %vl = current lines
 *         %vo = current online time
 *         %vr = current rxd bytes
 *         %vt = current txd bytes
 *         %vu = current serial unit
 *         %vy = current serial unit+1
 *
 *         \p  = current password        only for compatibility!
 *         %rb = current bbs name
 *         %rc = current cost           (xxx.xx)
 *         %rd = current download dir
 *         %re = current emulation      (Ansi/VT,Hex,XEm 2.0)
 *         %rf = current port flags     (8n1)
 *         %rh = current cts/rts/online (CRO)
 *         %ri = current font name
 *         %rl = current protocol
 *         %rm = current phone
 *         %ro = current online time    (00:00:00)
 *         %rp = current password
 *         %rr = current rxd bytes      (xxxxxB,xxxxkB,xxxxMB)
 *         %rs = current system time    (00:00:00)
 *         %rt = current txd bytes      (xxxxxB,xxxxkB,xxxxMB)
 *         %ru = current upload dir
 *         %rv = current serial device
 *         %rx = current pubscreen name (always used screen!)
 *
 * return: -
 *

This is in effect only for strings which are sent to serial.

 ~  - 0.5 second pause, use \~ for real ~ char.

 These two codes are no longer supported:

 \m - select menu, format is \mmenu!item!subitem!.
 \d - run dos command, format is \d'command arguments'
@endnode

@node "doc_tooltypes" "Tooltypes"
Look at DreamTerm icon as it has all tooltypes in inactive state.

Action kind tooltypes

 DIAL   = Start dialing phonebook entry which name matches, case insensitive.

Changing variables

 ASYNCIO  use asyncio.library for io.
 LOCALE = language to use, if not provided system default language is used.
 DEF_ALL= default base string for DEF_xx, means that used unless DEF_xx
          is provided. Defaults to DT_config.
 DEF_CS = default charset
 DEF_CU = default current settings
 DEF_GL = default profile (.g1 & .g2)
 DEF_PB = default phonebook & droplist (.pb & .dl)
 DEF_SL = default showlist
 DEF_TB = default toolbar
 DEF_XM = default xem
 DEF_XP = default protocol

 Note that DEF_xx values have maximum lenght of 60 chars and suffix must not
 be added as it is handled automatically.

 Some words about asyncio.library... In my experience this library works ok
 but it may be that it won't work with you machine, that is only reason
 why it is by default turned off. Try it and if it works use it, as it is
 much better than crappy dos.library routines. (Well, so that you know; this
 revision of library is first in my knowledge to actually work:-)

Internal variables, normally you should not use these at all as they are very
critical and can decrease performane greatly if changed.

 CAPSIZE   = internal capture buffer size (8192)
 TXDSIZE   = internal txd buffer size     (4096)
 POOL_TYPE = internal mem type            (MEMF_ANY)
 POOL_SIZE = internal puddle size         (16384)
 POOL_TRES = internal threshold           (8192)
@endnode

@node "doc_history" "History"
 (ADDED ) - Added feature/option
 (CHANGE) - Changed feature/option
 (BUGFIX) - Fixed some annoying bug
 (BETTER) - Optimized feature/option (obsolete)
 (REMOVE) - Removed feature/option   (obsolete)

@{u}V1.50 : 17-Apr-96 166132 bytes@{uu}

 (ADDED ) Several tooltypes.
 (ADDED ) Save for review and keyboard control for it.
 (ADDED ) Possibility to use standalone protocols.
 (ADDED ) New string codes, you can also now format them etc.
 (ADDED ) Option to use shared serial.
 (ADDED ) Option to use asyncio.library for fileoperations.
 (CHANGE) Status line format can be configured.
 (CHANGE) Internal ansi emulation should be little bit more compactible,
          however partial scroll is not supported.
 (CHANGE) ARexx commands are removed in time being, shouldn't be big loss
          as they weren't even documented... I'll add them back as soon as
          I have time to learn arexx little more :-)
 (CHANGE) Double buffer option now affects also XPr2.001 (aka DModem)
          protocols.
 (CHANGE) File transfer is now done in childtask, not sure if it is smart
          way to do it but helped to support standalone protocols.
 (CHANGE) Some windows are now internally classes, whatever it means. As
          all ain't ready yet (I change them as I have time/interest) there
          is currently some duplicate code to do same things... :)
 (CHANGE) Dispose window objects no longer works with all objects, due
          internal way of handling things it could create strange gurus
          with requesters etc.
 (BUGFIX) Some modem strings were not translated.
 (BUGFIX) Hardware serial signals were inaccurate, propably didn't break
          anything but fixed it anyway.
 (BUGFIX) Auto upload/download was used even when you did not specify string.
 (BUGFIX) Review didn't free its buffer, seems to be due pooled allocations
          which didn't free pools for some reason. Anyway now works and also
          should use little bit less memory.
 (BUGFIX) Upload list was not printed in reopen (if dispose was on).
 (BUGFIX) Hardware serial buffer was mistakenly allocated as MEMF_ANY.
 (BUGFIX) Priority was not changed back when exiting, only affected if
          started from shell.

@{u}V1.49 : 16-Feb-96 155152 bytes@{uu}

 (ADDED ) Localization, english and finnish are currently available.
 (CHANGE) Review is rewritted and uses dynamic memory allocation, save is
          removed in this version as I'm going to rewrite request code.
 (BUGFIX) Logfile avr. cps was written even when normal serial was in use,
          due this logfile entry was corrupted with berserk value.
 (BUGFIX) Normal serial device routines had small bug which could make
          up/download impossible, I just can't believe that nobody reported
          this in about year or two. Only possible explanation is that
          none uses this crap program. :( Well, if it still bugs try to use
          hardware serial.
 (BUGFIX) Phonebook open crashed if showlist was empty.
 (BUGFIX) ExecBase ($4.w) was mistakenly used instead of SysBase "cache".
 (BUGFIX) Hardware serial now shows right cps value in any screenmode though
          it can be slightly inaccurate.

@{u}V1.48 : 14-Dec-95 162204 bytes@{uu}

 (CHANGE) Phonebook sort by slider is changed back to cycle gadget.
 (BUGFIX) Dialer window texts flickered, I tracked this down long time
          before I noticed that for some reason MUI will send signal about
          8 times per second when MUI window is open, due that texts were
          refreshed too often. Should have not trusted my once per second
          timer signal. However I wonder why MUI signals program as it
          don't send anything to program during these 'idle' signals.
 (BUGFIX) Crashed if iconified during file transfer and not in online.
 (BUGFIX) CPS class trashed display in some cases, nothing dangerous though.
 (BUGFIX) Hardware screen was broken totally.
 (BUGFIX) Warning bugged with MUI3.1, seems to be MUI bug.

@{u}V1.47 : 30-Nov-95 161708 bytes@{uu}

 (ADDED ) Option to choose if window objects should be created/deleted
          everytime when used. This will save a lot of memory and will
          also speed up startup.
 (ADDED ) Configurable graphics buttons (toolbar), macros are removed.
 (CHANGE) Stack usage is much lower, to be safe use still at least 16384.
 (CHANGE) Pickup table name is changed to profile.
 (CHANGE) Phonebook can be now configured to show almost any data from entry.
 (CHANGE) Console window now has resize gadget in public screen mode.
 (CHANGE) Initstring and password will not automatically add return (\r)
          to end anymore. You must reconfigure your phonebook and
          initstring.
 (BETTER) Documentation is merged with help file and should be little
          bit more readable, also some things are explained first time. :)
 (BUGFIX) Hex emulation now works correctly with all console sizes.
 (BUGFIX) Small bug caused memory loss during running, all was freed at
          the end.
 (BUGFIX) Download path menu had wrong text.

@{b}V1.46 @{ub}:@{b} 15-Jan-95@{ub} 133612 bytes

 (ADDED ) Minimal collection of useless arexx commands.
 (CHANGE) You can now add files to upload queue during upload.
 (CHANGE) 'OK' response code is now skip condition in dialer.
 (CHANGE) Autosafe saves now 3 generations (.old/.oldest).
 (CHANGE) Upload list will discard duplicate files.
 (BUGFIX) Dialer could lose response codes if pickup table was edited during
          dialing.
 (BUGFIX) Upload list total size was sometimes wrong.
 (BUGFIX) Statusline size was added to public screen window size.
 (BUGFIX) Review save used 0 for linefeed.
 (BUGFIX) Status line was opened to public screen.
 (BUGFIX) If screen open failed then next screen open tried to close Wb.
 (BUGFIX) Sendascii leave some menus disabled.

@{b}V1.45 : 16-Nov-94@{ub} 131628 bytes

 (ADDED ) Possibility to temporarily lock phonebook entry.
 (ADDED ) Macros.
 (BUGFIX) Screen reopen leaded to lockup in certain cases.
 (BUGFIX) Review save didn't work.
 (BUGFIX) XEm color allocation was slightly broken.
 (BUGFIX) Transfer window was not activated with hardware screen.
 (BUGFIX) Quit didn't warn about online status.
 (BUGFIX) Menu disable/enable was not perfect.

@{b}V1.44 : 14-Oct-­94@{ub} 129992 bytes

 (ADDED ) Possibility to override columns/lines and use screenmode requester
          for console size.
 (ADDED ) Overscan type and autoscroll.
 (CHANGE) In XEm configuration it is now possible to define how many colors
          are allocated.
 (BUGFIX) Download list generated some additional spaces after bbs name.

@{b}V1.43 : 29-Sep-94@{ub} 128228 bytes

 (ADDED ) BorderBlank.
 (ADDED ) Serial release.
 (ADDED ) \\d and \\m.
 (ADDED ) Multiselect in menus.
 (ADDED ) Sort by selected in phonebook.
 (ADDED ) You can now open to any public screen not just on Workbench.
 (ADDED ) Serial buffer size.
 (ADDED ) Quit will warn if you want to quit while online.
 (ADDED ) Upload list can now give you estimations.
 (CHANGE) Transfer window will not abort if you try to close it, keyboard
          shortcuts are also removed.
 (CHANGE) Crypt phonebook now crypts every phonebook save expect save
          selected.
 (CHANGE) Requests are now asynchronous.
 (CHANGE) All requests expect Asl ones use now MUI.
 (CHANGE) ReqTools is no longer needed (Use ReqChange like me:^).
 (CHANGE) Entry window will look nicer with register group.
 (CHANGE) Prescroll is now ansi emulation option (as it should be).
 (CHANGE) Custom screen is now public.
 (BETTER) Change option works now in XEm configuration window, previous
          version didn't work because most XEm libraries will not change
          their options if you call XEmulatorPreferences() after
          XEmulatorOpenConsole()...
 (BETTER) All options should be in disabled state when you cannot change
          them, this was not 100% in previous version and created some
          problems.
 (BETTER) Review buffer is now line-oriented.
 (BUGFIX) Entry window generated some unwanted notify's.
 (BUGFIX) Proportional font created some misaligned text fields in GUI.
 (BUGFIX) Sometimes crashed if you changed up/dn paths during transfer.
 (BUGFIX) Hardware serial failed sometimes.
 (BUGFIX) DOSBase was closed twice.
 (BUGFIX) Logfile write used some wrong commands (nothing serious).
 (BUGFIX) Charset add didn't work if there was no selected entry.
 (BUGFIX) Wait and pause weren't changing when dialing.

@{b}V1.42 : 20-Jul-94@{ub} 133852 bytes

(BUGFIX) Interactive xpr setting was broken.

@{b}V1.41 : 18-Jul-94@{ub} 133852 bytes

 (ADDED ) Prescroll.
 (ADDED ) In protocol config you can use also interactive setting instead of
          initstring if protocol supports it.
 (ADDED ) Shift cursor.
 (ADDED ) Various modem strings.
 (REMOVE) No more custom scrolling.
 (CHANGE) No space between dial prefix and phone number anymore.
 (CHANGE) Capture versions of conversion files will now strip some controls.
 (CHANGE) Phone entry window is hopefully easier to use.
 (BUGFIX) SendAscii also converted \\n etc.
 (BUGFIX) CTRL-] (^]) etc. didn't work.
 (BUGFIX) XEm keys weren't working.
 (BUGFIX) Crashed if you tried to upload using empty list.

@{b}V1.4 : 03-May-94@{ub} 136648 bytes

 (ADDED ) XEM support (and lots of bugs with it).
 (ADDED ) Capture and review buffer.
 (ADDED ) Possibility to crypt phonebook using xpk. Remember that forces of
          evil (or good as they claim) are always snooping around.
 (CHANGE) Fileid is now upload list.
 (CHANGE) Default ZPriv is removed from protocols.
 (BETTER) Optimized code a bit making code more compact and smaller.
 (BETTER) Changed Ansi-C memory/file functions to Amiga ones.
 (BUGFIX) Failed try to open xpr library disabled xpr. 
 (BUGFIX) Chars ^ and / were stripped if entered from keyboard.
 (BUGFIX) You could not set listview or emulation to global state.
 (BUGFIX) Interface was messy with proportional font.
 (BUGFIX) Dial number could crash machine and prefix was added to number.
 (BUGFIX) Software serial crashed if device couldn't be opened.
 (BUGFIX) Total hardware serial lockup if you used xpr protocol and double
          buffer was off or protocol sent more than 2048 chars at once.
 (BUGFIX) Pickup phone prefix requester was canceled if you entered empty
          string.
 (BUGFIX) I experienced some mysterious crashes with large droplist but this
          version seems to be working, not actually sure if I fixed it...

@{b}V1.3 : 20-Feb-94 (sort of panic version)@{ub} 164120 bytes

 (ADDED ) Different sort categories in phonebook.
 (BETTER) Now using MUI 2.0.
 (BETTER) Multitasks better, previous versions used something like 'sliced'
          CPU which leaded to massive CPU usage...
 (BUGFIX) MUI images/background changed colors after changing screen depth
          (or pens). This is __MUI__ bug but fortunately I found a way to
          correct this.
 (BUGFIX) ANSI cursor save/recall was not recalling cursor position more
          than once.
 (BUGFIX) In 2-8 color screen it was hard to read some requester texts
          because they used background color... :)
 (BUGFIX) Droplist compare was not working fully.
 (BUGFIX) Some gadgets were not in MUI tabcycle.

 @{b}V1.2 : 12-Feb-94 @{ub}162368 bytes@{b}
