@node "doc_future" "Empty promises"
I have thousands of ideas but as I do this for free and for fun you shouldn't
expect very speedy time table. :-)

        Implementing version: 1.50

        Version number indicates when implementation was done. Note: do not
        care about finnish text, this is extracted from my private todo list.

future plans:

        - maybe remove hardware screen, kinda useless
        - rework gui, major hassle: changing many things to be classes
        - pure
        - option to show phonenumbers in separate lines
        - automatic stack set
        - more graphical outlook (should code some classes for that)
        - possibility to edit entry also when it is online
          (in fact all should be possible to edit also when they are in use)
        - profile name for entry window
        - multiedit for phonebook (tricky as hard to do simple one which
          is readable with different profiles etc. argh...)
        - useful arexx commands (not in priority 1)
        - status window
        - upload loglist
        - possibility to remember downloaded names (+use it to autoskip etc.)
        - traps
        - possibility to create unlimited number of profiles (old
          pickuptables, it will be mess, must think about it)
        - create entry from current settings
        - possibility to remove dial entry (number?) when dialing
        - add cr->lf, lf->cr
        - IEMSI (this would be easy with good arexx commands)
        - Optio jolla dialointi aika lisätään connect aikaan
        - Optio jolla serialia ei vapauteta iconifyn aikana
        - error count to xpr status
        - packet window (stealed from Term:-)
        - connection cost table (automaaginen numeron avulla)
        - conversion tablea voidaan myös editoida (ei tarvitse ladata)
        - qualifers for cursor / funcs
        - review search
        - keymap defination
        - mahdollisuus määritellä system penit tai käyttää Wb:n kyniä.
        - droplistaan mahdollisuus muistaa myös bbs nimi/phone/password etc.
          + mahdollisuus kopioida takaisin...
        - disconnect action, serial, dos
        - connect action, serial, dos
        - file downloaded dos
        - droplist format is changed, old one should be converted
          automatically.

Changes:

        - whole code should be cleaned and reorder routines & structure
          of program. currently it is a MESS.
        - option for console to be MUI object (not hard but XEm would need
          major hacking). Actually I could rewrite those pd sources...
        - enviroment (env) options should have own window (remove menus?)

Bugfixes:

 *!!*   - all dir reqs disable console (ReqChange bug!)
        - xfer window progress bar bugs after 3.5M... (mui bug?)
        - reqs open to wb if public screen is other than wb (report)
        - window change leaves some unwanted gfx to screen
        - sendtranslate() do not change cr->crlf etc.
        - hm, why the hell txd cr/lf translate is in screen menu ?!
        - if console is in public screen and some req open it will not warn
          its state when changing screen, ie. dterm should put up message to
          signal user to close that req... (argh, I won't fix this as making
          things to be classes will fix this later)
@endnode

@node "menu_main" "Menus bars"

 @{" Project " link "menu_project" 0} @{" Phonebook " link "menu_phonebook" 0} @{" Transfer " link "menu_transfer" 0} @{" Serial " link "menu_serial" 0} @{" Screen " link "menu_screen" 0} @{" Emulation " link "menu_emulation" 0} @{" Special " link "menu_special" 0}

Notice that most menus are just shortcuts for changing current settings, only
very few of them are used to change @{"global settings" link "doc_terminology" 0} or start some action. To
help you know what menu actually does there is keyword in first line of the
menu description. There is also some current settings which can't be changed
from menus, for them you must use @{"Current settings..." link "help_entry" 0} window. This is little
bit confusing and I propably gather all global settings to one big window
someday.

Keywords:

 @{u} action @{uu} menu item which starts some action.
 @{u} global @{uu} menu item which changes global settings.

And if there is nothing then menu item is used to change current settings.
@endnode

