@node "menu_project_profile phone pre" "Project menu: Profile phone prefix... "
This is just quick way of changing profile's @{"phone number prefix" link "help_bbs_phone number prefix" 0}.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_load configuratio" "Project menu: Load configuration      "
@{u} action @{uu}

Load default charset, protocol, external emulation, toolbar and profile and
discard old ones, all will be loaded from current directory. If you started
from Workbench it is same where DreamTerm is, if from shell then it is
directory where you were when you launched DreamTerm.

Currently these files will be used, though you can configure them by using
@{"tooltypes" link "doc_tooltypes" 0}.

 dt_config.cs   - character set configuration      (DEF_CS)
 dt_config.g1   - profile                          (DEF_GL)
 dt_config.g2   - default pick from profile        (DEF_DL)
 dt_config.tb   - toolbar configuration            (DEF_TB)
 dt_config.xp   - protocol configuration           (DEF_XP)
 dt_config.xm   - external emulation configuration (DEF_XM)
@endnode

@node "menu_project_save configuratio" "Project menu: Save configuration      "
@{u} action @{uu}

Save default charset, protocol, external emulation, toolbar, profile and
current settings, all will be saved to current directory. If you started from
Workbench it is same where DreamTerm is, in shell start it is directory where
you were when you launched DreamTerm. Note that current settings will be used
only when you next time start DreamTerm. If you have @{"phonebook crypting" link "menu_project_phonebook cryptin" 0} option
on then bbs name, phone number, password and function keys will be deleted
from current settings.

Currently these files will be used, though you can configure them by using
@{"tooltypes" link "doc_tooltypes" 0}.

 dt_config.cs   - character set configuration      (DEF_CS)
 dt_config.cu   - current configuration            (DEF_CU)
 dt_config.g1   - profile                          (DEF_GL)
 dt_config.g2   - default pick from profile        (DEF_GL)
 dt_config.tb   - toolbar configuration            (DEF_TB)
 dt_config.xp   - protocol configuration           (DEF_XP)
 dt_config.xm   - external emulation configuration (DEF_XM)
@endnode

@node "menu_project_titlebar" "Project menu: TitleBar                "
@{u} action @{uu}

This will toggle titlebar on/of, making possible to change screen place if
needed. If you not already know you can also use left amiga to move screen,
just press it down and move your mouse.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_temporary directo" "Project menu: Temporary directory     "
@{u} global @{uu}

This will pop up requester where you can choose which directory to use to save
temporary files, these are created during phonebook crypting and when XEm2.0
is used.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_initstring" "Project menu: InitString              "
@{u} global @{uu}

This string will be sent to modem when DreamTerm started. All normal string
@{"commands" link "doc_string commands" 0} can be used.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_phonebook cryptin" "Project menu: Phonebook crypting      "
@{u} global @{uu}

If you think that someone may be interested what your phonebook contains set
this on, will also remove name, phone, password and function keys from current
settings.

NOTE: If @{"auto phonebook save" link "menu_project_auto phonebook sa" 0} was on then backup files are still uncrypted! You
must save config & default phonebook, quit DreamTerm and run it twice to make
them crypted.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_auto phonebook sa" "Project menu: Auto phonebook save     "
@{u} global @{uu}

When this option is on DreamTerm will save default phonebook to disk after you
have disconnected from bbs.  This is handy if you want to make sure that last
call etc. information is up to date, it is very easy to forget to save default
phonebook before quitting. However keep this is in mind when editing you
phonebook so you don't accidentally lose entries if you happen to call in
midst of heavy entry deleting. Due this there is little extra safety feature
in this option; default phonebook will be copied in startup.

 dt_config.pb.old -> dt_config.pb.oldest
 dt_config.pb     -> dt_config.pb.old

Remember that you need 7-wire serial cable with carrier signal line for this
to work.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_dispose window ob" "Project menu: Dispose window objects"
@{u} global @{uu}

If this is on every object is created only when used, it will save memory and
will allow flushing MUI libraries. However this will slow window opening and
for example entry window may take few seconds to open. Note that you may not
notice that program uses less memory as all MUI objects are loaded as
libraries and they will stay in memory unless flushed, this will happen only
if memory is otherwise used or you flush libraries.

NEWSFLASH: Due many things which won't be discussed here this option will
propably be removed in next version.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_about" "About                   "
@{u} action @{uu}

This will open window which will show current version of DreamTerm, its
compile date and some useless information.
@endnode

@node "menu_project_quit" "Quit"
@{u} action @{uu}

This will quit DreamTerm, however if you have changed some configuration and
haven't saved it or you are online there will be warning.
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook" "Phonebook"
 @{"Directory...          " link "help_pb" 0}
 @{"Create entry...       " link "help_entry" 0}
 @{"Load default phonebook" link "menu_phonebook_load_default_ph" 0}
