 @{"Dial next selected    " link "menu_phonebook_dial_next_selec" 0}
 @{"Send current password " link "menu_phonebook_send current pa" 0}
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook_load_default_ph" "Load default phonebook"
@{u} action @{uu}

Load default phonebook, droplist and showlist, all will be loaded from current
directory. If you started from Workbench it is same where DreamTerm is, if
from shell then it is directory where you were when you launched DreamTerm.

Currently these files will be used, though you can change them using
@{"tooltypes" link "doc_tooltypes" 0}.

 dt_config.pb   - phonebook (DEF_PB)
 dt_config.dl   - droplist  (DEF_PB)
 dt_config.sl   - showlist  (DEF_SL)
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook_save_default_ph" "Save default phonebook"
@{u} action @{uu}

Save default phonebook, droplist and showlist, all will be saved to current
directory. If you started from Workbench it is same where DreamTerm is, if
from shell then it is directory where you were when you launched DreamTerm.

Currently these files will be used, though you can change them by using
@{"tooltypes" link "doc_tooltypes" 0}.

 dt_config.pb   - phonebook (DEF_PB)
 dt_config.dl   - droplist  (DEF_PB)
 dt_config.sl   - showlist  (DEF_SL)
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook_dial_number" "Dial number"
@{u} action @{uu}

Pop ups requester where you can choose which number to dial, note that current
settings are used for that call.
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook_dial_next_selec" "Dial next selected"
@{u} action @{uu}

Start to dial selected entries in phonebook.
@endnode

@node "menu_phonebook_send current pa" "Send current password "
@{u} action @{uu}

This will send current password to host, no additional chars are sent after it
so you should add \r (return) at the end of string.
@endnode

