@node "menu_serial_serial active" "Serial active"
@{u} action @{uu}

When this is checked then serial routines are in use, unchecking this will
have slightly different procedures depending you serial settings. Normally
this will close serial device which leads to dropping of DTR which may cause
hangup depending your modem settings. However if you have shared serial option
on then this will simply disable all serial activity and thus should allow
other serial using program to work.

Note: Running external protocol will do exactly same procedure when runned.
@endnode

@node "menu_serial_hangup" "Hangup"
@{u} action @{uu}

Hangup modem. If @{"Drop DTR to hangup" link "help_serial_drop_dtr_to_hangup" 0} option is on then DTR is just dropped for
a moment, otherwise configurable @{"hangup string" link "help_modem_hangup" 0} is sent to modem.
@endnode

