Selected means entries which has number in front of them (ie. you have double
clicked them), cursored is entry where cursor is.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_showlist" "Showlist"
Which showlist to use view phonebook listview, you can @{"edit showlist" link "help_sl" 0} so that
almost every information from phonebook entry can be viewed in listview but
keep in mind that every field will take additional time to draw.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_sort_by" "Sort by"
This will have names of different fields seen in listview and additional
selected field. Just choose one and phonebook listview will be sorted by it.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_sort_mode" "Sort mode"
You can choose either ascending or descending sort mode.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_dial" "Dial"
Close phonebook window and start to dial selected entries.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_unselect" "Unselect"
Unselect all selected entries.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_add" "Add"
Add new entry to phonebook, look @{"here" link "help_entry" 0} for more info.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_clone" "Clone"
Create new entry from cursored entry, look @{"here" link "help_entry" 0} from more info.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_edit" "Edit"
Edit cursored entry.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_delete" "Delete"
Delete cursored entry.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_drop_away" "Drop away"
Delete cursored entry and move its phonenumbers to @{"droplist" link "help_dl" 0}.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_freeze" "Freeze"
Bad modem addiction? Impossible not to hit @{"Dial" link "help_pb_dial" 0} button again and again until
you are in same condition as late C= was? Here is answer, just freeze entry
for 1-720 hours and you cannot select entry, voila burden of decision is
removed from you... However be careful as system clock must be in right time
or else your entry may be freezed forever.
@endnode

@node "help_pb_reset" "Reset"
Remove additional information from entry, in short these are removed:

 Last called
 Total time
 Total cost
 Total calls
 Sent bytes
 Received bytes
@endnode

@node "help_dl" "Droplist"

                    +----------------------------+
                    |                            |
                    |                            |
                    |                            |
                    |                            |
                    +----------------------------+
                          Add           Delete     

With this window you can edit droplist, it contains only name and it is phone
number. When you create new entries in phonebook then its phonenumbers are
compared against this list, if entry has at least one number which is exactly
same than in this list then you are prompted warning. Note that compare do not
use @{"phone number prefix" link "help_bbs_phone number prefix" 0}!

Idea is that you use drop away button to move entrys phonenumbers here and
thus if you later accidentally try to add bbs system again in your list you
get warning. This also is handy when using automatic phonenumber adder
(Laho2Pb).

This list is automatically loaded during startup, of course you can save it
using @{"Save default phonebook" link "menu_phonebook_save_default_ph" 0} menuitem and load using @{"Load default phonebook" link "menu_phonebook_load_default_ph" 0}
menuitem. However keep in mind that those actions will load phonebook too.
@endnode

@node "help_sl" "Showlist"
 Showlist
  @{"Load         " link "help_base_general_load" 0}  +------+ +-----------------+
  @{"Save         " link "help_base_general_save" 0}  |@{"      " link "help_base_general_lv" 0}| |@{"                 " link "help_sl_lv_tag" 0}|
  @{"Append       " link "help_base_general_append" 0}  |      | |                 | 
  @{"Save selected" link "help_base_general_save_selecte" 0}  |      | +-----------------+
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~  |      | Control @{"-----------" link "help_sl_control" 0}
  @{"Close        " link "help_base_general_close" 0}  +------+ Move up  Move down
                 -------- Add tag  Delete tag
                 @{"     Add     " link "help_base_general_add" 0} @{"    Delete    " link "help_base_general_delete" 0}

With this window you create/edit showlists for phonebook, one list contains a
name and tag list which defines what information to show from phonebook entry.
Currently you can configure only 64 tags as MUI restricts it. List which is
currently in use cannot be edited. Also bear in mind that all changes are
immediately on effect. 

Note: Currently PhoneBook will use first list when starting, this will be
removed in some version.
@endnode

@node "help_sl_lv_tag" "Tags"
This will show what information is printed in fields 1-63, 0 is always
selected status.
@endnode

@node "help_sl_control" "Control"
This controls how to show information in phonebook listview and every item
can(must) be configured individually. Anyway, this is just a string which may
contain listview template and/or MUI text engine commands.

Extract from MUI listview documentation:

        The template for a single entry looks like this:

        DELTA=D/N,PREPARSE=P/K,WEIGHT=W/N,
        MINWIDTH=MIW/N,MAXWIDTH=MAW/N,COL=C/N

        DELTA
           Space in pixel between this column and the next.
           the last displayed column ignores this setting.
           Defaults to 4.

        PREPARSE
           A preparse value for this column. Setting this
           e.g. to "\33c" would make the column centered.

        WEIGHT
           The weight of the column. As with MUI's group
           class, columns are layouted with a minimum
           size, a maximum size and weight. A column with
           a weight of 200 would gain twice the space than
           a column with a weight of 100.
           Defaults to 100.

        MINWIDTH
           Minimum percentage width for the current column.
           If your list is 200 pixel wide and you set this
           to 25, your column will at least be 50 pixel.
           The special value -1 for this parameter means that
           the minimum width is as wide as the widest entry in
           this column. This ensures that every entry will be
           completely visible (as long as the list is wide enough).
           Defaults to -1.

        MAXWIDTH
           Maximum percentage width for the current column.
           If your list is 200 pixel wide and you set this
           to 25, your column will not be wider as 50 pixel.
           The special value -1 for this parameter means that
           the maximum width is as wide as the widest entry in
           this column.
           Defaults to -1.

        COL
           This value adjusts the number of the current column.
           This allows you to adjust the order of your columns
           without having to change your display hook. See
           example for details.
           Defaults to current entry number (0,1,...)

Extract from MUI text documentation (only usable in PREPARSE):

        '\n'     Start a new line. With this character you can e.g.
                 create multi line buttons.

        ESC -    Disable text engine, following chars will be printed
                 without further parsing.

        ESC u    Set the soft style to underline.

        ESC b    Set the soft style to bold.

        ESC i    Set the soft style to italic.

        ESC n    Set the soft style back to normal.

        ESC <n>  Use pen number n (2..9) as front pen. n must be a valid

        ESC c    Center current (and following) line(s).
                 This sequence is only valid at the beginning of a
                 string or after a newline character.

        ESC r    Right justify current (and following) line(s).
                 This sequence is only valid at the beginning of a
                 string or after a newline character.

        ESC l    Left justify current (and following) line(s).
                 This sequence is only valid at the beginning of a
                 string or after a newline character.

        ESC I[s] Draw MUI image with specification <s>. See autodocs
                 of image class for image spec definition.

However as C uses octal for \xx you MUST use \27 (ESC) instead of \33 in those
examples. Note that you can use text commands (those with ESC x) only in
template P= (PREPARSE), also you should not use COL keyword as it will not
work right. This way of handling things offers maximum flexibility and minimum
coding (and maximum user difficulty:-). Actually this implementation is
directly from user_must_suffer manual...
@endnode

